30/01/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- KosovaLive on Thursday (29 January) quoted NATO Ambassador to Skopje Nicolaas Biegman as saying the security situation in Kosovo has normalised.
After meeting with Kosovo Parliament Speaker Nexhat Daci, Biegman reportedly said that the situation in the province has much improved over the past two years, crediting KFOR's pivotal role in stabilising the situation.
Maintaining good neighbourly ties with Macedonia is essential, he stressed.
(BBC - 30/01/04;
KosovaLive - 29/01/04)
